<p>â€œBack in the day, Walter would, every once in a while, forget how to draw. Remember?â€ Louise said.Â </p>

<p>â€œOh yeah,â€ Walter agreed. â€œThat still happens occasionally. Itâ€™s like, â€˜Oh my god, nothing Iâ€™m drawing looks any good anymore. My life is over as an artist.â€™ And what I realized, because I was an editor at the time, and had seen a lot of work go past me, was that when you hit this phase where suddenly your stuff, which looks just like it did yesterday, doesnâ€™t look good to you anymore, itâ€™s because your mind has made a leap. Your brain has gotten farther than your hand has learned to do it yet. But eventually, give it a few weeks, keep it up and youâ€™ve made a leap in your own craft. That was a big help because it was so depressing when you realize you couldnâ€™t draw anymore.â€Â </p>

