I can hear him saying the same thing now. And saying, too, as he did that night over cactus soup, â€œThereâ€™s a thread that runs through poetry, or that is supposed to, and thatâ€™s truth.â€ I was writing down everything he said on the back of my Kenneth Koch eulogy. 
â€œThe problem with students,â€ Derek continued, â€œis that theyâ€™re not taught love.â€ 
I said, â€œIn life, you mean?â€ And he said, â€œIn poetry.â€ 
One of the many lessons Derek Walcott taught us was how to watch and listen for the overlap between the two.</p>

