<p>Writing isnâ€™t easy</p>

<p>That hard work is as important as creativity.Â Various anecdotes and biopics have created the impression that good writers are able to conjure great novels and poems from pure inspiration, thatâ€™s why a lot of people assume that writers have an easy life.Â     The reality is very different as it takes a great deal of hard work to craft a coherent novel, let alone a great one.
