<p>I tend to read new books more-often than I reread, but there are some I return to over and over:</p>
<ol>
  <li>â€œThe Great Gatsbyâ€ by F. Scott Fitzgerald. I am one of many people for whom itâ€™s a perfect novel. Iâ€™m an atheist, but if anything could make me believe in God, itâ€™s this book. I donâ€™t see how a human can reach that level of perfection. Itâ€™s also a writing manual for me. Each time I read it (at least once a year, and I also listen to audiobook versions of it), I learn new techniques.</li>
